item.title: Caring for the children of the stars
item.dc:creator: silinwang123
item.content:encoded:
There is such a group of children, they are like the twinkling stars in the distant sky, far away from our real life. Such children are called "children of the stars", "children of the stars" live in their own world like the stars in the sky . People describe autistic children like this: they are not deaf, but they are deaf to the sound; they are not blind, but they are blind to people and things around them; they are not dumb, but they don't know how to speak. They are like stars in the sky alone in a world, and they have a common name-children with autism. Every year, April 2 is the world "Autistic Child Care Day". For autism, misunderstanding and ignorance are often the biggest obstacles to social recognition and support. Children with autism should have equal opportunities for development. , Enjoy a normalized life.

In order to let more people understand and pay attention to children with autism, and let everyone’s love warm their loneliness, ASG calls on the whole society to pay attention to patients with autism, deepen society’s understanding of children with autism, and cultivate a conducive to The good social and cultural atmosphere for the healthy growth of special children provides them with a better social environment. Let us join hands to care for the children of these stars!

item.dc:creator: silinwang123
item.content:encoded:
Adults’ Group for People with ASD

Formed in November 2010, the group meets on the first Saturday of the month around 6:00pm. The meet-up provides an opportunity for adults with ASD to interact with one another and other community members.

The Adolescents’ Group

Formed in April 2010, a social group of young people aged between 12 to 17 years meets on the last Sunday of the month. Activities include cooking, handicrafts, xbox gaming and a variety of board games.

IT Group

Recently formed! If you are in high school or a young adult (to age 20), interested in game design, social media or web design. You may like to join a group of other like-minded young people to learn more and share ideas in technology. This group will meet from 2:00 pm – 4:00 pm on the second Sunday of the month.

Brothers and Sisters (or Siblings) Group

Open to all school-age children who have a sister or brother who is on the autism spectrum. This group meets once a term to renew friendships and to share, through social outings and play, what it means to have a brother or sister with autism. These social outings are often conducted during school vacation periods.

Coffee Morning

Every last Friday of the month from 10 am to noon at McDonald’s, the group hosts coffee morning for parents and others interested in autism to share their experiences and learn more about autism.

item.title: BLOG
item.dc:creator: silinwang123
item.content:encoded:
Autism, also known as autism, is a severe generalized developmental disorder of infants. Children with typical symptoms will appear before the age of three. Essential interpersonal communication difficulties prevent them from establishing normal interpersonal relationships with other people, even their parents, using language, expressions, and movements. The concept of autism was proposed and determined by American psychiatrist Leo Kanner in 1943. But the phenomenon of autism existed before its concept was confirmed. It can be said that autism has a long past. <Details>

Cause：The cause of autism has not yet been fully elucidated. It may be related to the following factors, or it may develop under the combined action of multiple factors. 1. Genetic factors: Some children are related to genetic factors, and the role of genetic factors on autism has become clear. Among the siblings of children with this disease, 2% to 6% suffer from the disease. 36%.<Details>

Early intervention for autism：Childhood autism is a widespread developmental disorder. Autism usually starts before the age of three. So far, the cause of autism has not been understood, but studies have found that childhood autism is a biologically based disease that is highly related to genetic inheritance. Although we currently don’t have an immediate and effective treatment method, it is not without a cure for autism. <Details>

Diagnostic criteria：According to page 299 of the Fourth Edition of the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders, autism is defined as: A: has the following six characteristics (1), (2) and (3), of which at least two are from (1), (2) ) And (3) each have one item: (1) Lack of social skills, manifested in the lack of eye contact and no eye contact in at least two of the following. <Details>

item.title: 自我介绍（示例文章）
item.dc:creator: silinwang123
item.content:encoded:
这是一篇示例文章，最初作为 Blogging University 的组成部分发布。报名参加我们十个项目中的其中一个，立即开始撰写您的博客。

您今天要发布一篇文章。不必担心您的博客的外观。如果您还没有给博客命名或是感到不知所措，也不必担心。只需点击“新文章”按钮，告诉我们您来此处的原因。

为什么要这样做？

  • 因为它能为新读者提供背景信息。让他们了解您是做什么的，他们为什么应该阅读您的博客。
  • 因为这将帮助您专注于自己对博客的想法，以及您想用博客来做什么。

文章可短可长，可以是对您的生活的个性化介绍或是博客宗旨说明，也可以是对未来的宣言或是对希望发布的内容类型的简要概述。

为了帮助您开始撰写，不妨思考以下几个问题：

  • 您为什么要公开写博客，而不是写个人日记？
  • 您认为您会写些什么话题？
  • 您想通过博客和谁联系？
  • 如果您的博客成功写到明年，您想要达到什么目标？

您并非一定要受此限制，博客的一个奇妙之处在于，随着我们学习、成长和与他人互动，它们是会不断演变的，不过如果知道从何处入手以及为何开始，这将会颇有益处，并且明确您的目标可能会激发您写其他一些文章的灵感。

不知道如何开始？只需写下您脑海中闪现的第一件事即可。Anne Lamott 是一位作家，大家都喜欢她写的书。她指出，你要允许自己写出“蹩脚的初稿”。Anne 提出了一个很好的观点，先开始写，之后再去考虑如何编辑。

在您准备发布时，给您的文章贴上三到五个标签来描述您博客的关注点 - 写作、摄影、小说、育儿、美食、汽车、电影、体育等。这些标签将帮助关注您话题的人在阅读器中找到您。确保添加“zerotohero”标签，这样其他新博主也可以找到您。
